Description: Creates interactive HTML labels for botanical and living plant 
    collections with built-in text-to-speech capabilities in multiple languages 
    (Portuguese, English, French, Spanish). The package extracts species data 
    from taxonomic databases (Flora e Funga do Brasil and Plants of the World 
    Online), handles synonym resolution, generates natural language descriptions, 
    and produces standalone HTML files with audio playback controls. Users can 
    optionally provide personal audio recordings that automatically take priority 
    over synthesized speech. The package includes interactive maps showing species 
    distribution at global and Brazilian state levels. Designed to expedite the 
    production of collection labels for arboreta, botanical gardens, and living 
    plant collections. Each label includes taxonomic information, distribution 
    data, habitat descriptions, and origin status, with the ability to listen 
    to descriptions using browser speech synthesis or custom recordings.
